# Error Handling

- Use structured error enums with explicit categories.
- Distinguish invalid requests from provider failures.
- Classify provider errors clearly: `Timeout`, `RateLimited`, `AuthenticationFailed`, `ProviderUnavailable`, and `ProviderBadResponse`.
- Keep retryable and non-retryable errors distinct.
- Never expose API keys, Authorization headers, full raw provider errors, or stack traces.
- Include `request_id` in client-facing error bodies when available.
- Map `InvalidRequest` to `400`, auth failures to `401` if auth exists, rate limits to `429`, upstream failures to `502`, no provider to `503`, timeouts to `504`, and unknown internal errors to `500`.
